Morphology. Cephalic characters largely similar to the male except for small compound eyes (
Figs 2
B–C). Wings similar to the male. Genitalia (
Fig. 4
): Subgenital plate (
Fig. 4B
), egg guide long, strongly sclerotized marginally and terminally round with long setae; ventral valve (
